Q2 VARIATION 3: O_NOFOLLOW applies only to final component
Condition twist:
Teacher checks POSIX-like behavior:
Open should still follow intermediate symlinks in path, but not final one when nofollow is set.

What changes conceptually:
Current simplistic open(path) + namei(path) gives final inode directly.
Need path-walk awareness of final component behavior.

Step-by-step:
1) In [kernel/sysfile.c](kernel/sysfile.c), parse path components manually (or via namex-style logic).
2) For each component except final:
   resolve symlinks normally.
3) At final component:
   if O_NOFOLLOW set and final inode is symlink, return symlink inode itself.
   if O_NOFOLLOW not set, follow as normal.
4) Keep depth guard for every symlink traversal.
5) Keep correct locking at each hop.
6) Directory write checks should apply to resolved inode according to mode.
7) Test cases:
   open("a/b/link", O_NOFOLLOW) where link is final => returns symlink inode.
   open("linkdir/file", O_NOFOLLOW) where linkdir is intermediate => still follow linkdir.

Why this works:
This matches nuanced open semantics often used for security checks.

Common trap:
Applying nofollow to all components and breaking intermediate path resolution.

